# BuildY (workspace)

**Role:** Browser workspace for prompt → plan → model → preview → source → export. Current slice is **fixture-driven UX mockups**, not production integrations.

## Stack

`github.com/fastygo/framework` + `github.com/fastygo/platform` + `github.com/fastygo/templ`

BuildY owns its starter UI shell, seeded from Blank patterns. **Do not add `@Blank` as a `go.mod` dependency.**

## UI rules

- Render from **BuildY-owned fixtures** — no hardcoded user-facing copy in templates.
- Compose with `github.com/fastygo/templ` (`ui/`, `components/`, `utils/`).
- Use BuildY's **`internal/ui/`** registry tree: `layout/`, `components/`, `blocks/`, `widgets/`, `variants/`, `utils/` — see `internal/ui/README.md`.
- Stage reusable sections in `internal/ui/blocks/<group>/`; promote to `fastygo/blocks` only after freeze — do not `require` blocks/widgets modules during mockup slice.
- App shell in `internal/ui/layout/`; home and workspace views in `internal/views/`.
- EN/RU via split fixtures (`site/*.json`, `screens/*.json`, `cms/*.json`).
- Dark theme, mobile menu, and language switch are mandatory for home mockup work.

## Out of scope (current slice)

- `github.com/fastygo/ui8kit`, `elements` — legacy Go modules, do not introduce.
- `github.com/fastygo/blocks`, `github.com/fastygo/widgets` as **dependencies** — not until post-mockup extraction; use `internal/ui/blocks/` and `internal/ui/widgets/` staging instead.
- Real GitHub App, billing, deploy, live AppCMS sync, sandbox code execution.
- Showcase app cards (AppCMS, AppCRM, AppSuite, Director, Contentor, Webmaster) as repo imports — presets in fixtures only.

## Plan workflow

Copy-paste implementation chunks: `.project/checklist-plan.md`  
Progress tracker: `.project/progress-ux-mockup-fixtures.md` — one Plan Chunk at a time.
